1 Microservices
1.1 Denion
Microservices have the architectural style that structures an applicaon as a collecon of independently
deployable services that are modeled around a business domain and are usually owned by a small team.

4 Controller .NET for API
4.1 What make the controller to be a controller
Has a sux of Controller in the name of the class and le
o Example: UserApiController
Derive from the ControllerBase class under namespace of Microso.AspNetCore. Mvc
o Example: public class UserApiController:ControllerBase
o A using statement is needed below:
Example: using Microso.AspNetCore.Mvc;
Need a controller aribute placed above the class
o Example: [ApiController]
p.5/6
Need a route aribute placed above the class
o Example: [Route("api/UserApi")] or [Route("api/[Controller]")]
4.2 What make an end point to be an end point
Need a verb aribute place above the funcon of the end point
o Example: [HpGet] or [HpGet({id:int})]
4.3 Handling return of status codes
Return type at the funcon of the end point should be AconResult<return type of object>, e.g.
AconResult<UserDto> and AconResult<IEnumerable<UserDto>>
Vericaon of the return value can specify the return status, e.g.:
o If(id == 0){return BadRequest()};
o If(user == null){return NotFound()};
o return Ok();
4.4 Document the return status of end point in Swagger
Aributes [ProducesResponseType(status code)] are needed for documenng the status above
the funcon of end point, e.g.
o [ProducesResponseType(200)] or [ProducesResponseType(StatusCodes.Status200OK)]
o [ProducesResponseType(400)] or
[ProducesResponseType(StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest)]
o [ProducesResponseType(404)] or
[ProducesResponseType(StatusCodes.Status404NotFound)]

Open Brace on New Line For Control Blocks

Open Brace on New Line For Funcons
5.2 If not .vscode folder generated
Generate the .vscode folder manually by opening your Command Palee (CTRL + SHIFT + P) and
then select .NET: Generate Assets For Build And Debug.
The .vscode folder has launch.json and tasks.json
6 Dotnet CLI commands
dotnet new list
o list all the template projects which can be built
dotnet new webapi -n <<project name>> -controllers
o create an webapi project with the given project name
p.6/6
dotnet new console name <<project name>>
o this creates an project with the name and also create a new folder holding the project
o if name <<project name>> is not provided, the project will be created in current folder
and the folder name will be the project name
o --use-program-main for not using top level statement (i.e. there is stac void
Main(string[] args) in program.cs)
